HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1094
By Lamberth
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Governor Lee on his deployment
of the National Guard to Memphis.
WHEREAS, in September 2025, President Donald Trump created the Memphis Safe
Task Force, whose objective is to "end street and violent crime in Memphis to the greatest
possible extent through the promotion and facilitation of hypervigilant policing, aggressive
prosecution, complex investigations, financial enforcement, and large-scale saturation of
besieged neighborhoods with law enforcement personnel"; and
WHEREAS, to aid in the objectives of the task force, Governor Bill Lee deployed
members of the Tennessee National Guard to assist local and federal law enforcement
agencies; and
WHEREAS, the deployment of the National Guard is credited with alleviating pressure
on the understaffed Memphis Police Department by acting as additional eyes and ears for law
enforcement; and
WHEREAS, the Memphis Safe Task Force has had incredible success in its mission,
including the arrest of over 4,000 criminals, the removal of more than 1,900 illegal firearms from
the streets, the reduction of murders and other violent crime in the city, the recovery of
thousands of stolen vehicles and other property, and the location and recovery of over 120
missing children; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we congratulate Governor Bill Lee on responding promptly to a grave
emergency by deploying the National Guard to Memphis in a successful effort to dramatically
lower the crime rate in the city.
